enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve removing expired entries from the map, which is a prerequisite for the entrySet method to return a consistent view of the map.
The now method provides the current time in milliseconds, which is used by the removeAllExpired method to determine which entries to remove before returning the entry set.
The entrySet method ultimately delegates to the superclass's entrySet method after removing expired entries, making it a direct source for assertions about the returned set.
The isExpired method is used to determine if entries are expired, which directly affects the contents of the entry set returned by the entrySet method.
